at|mitche: Bidding:   In third seat, the usual guidelines for a weak 2 bid are relaxed, so South's 2@d bid is perfectly 
normal -- even with a thin suit and few points.  West has a pretty good hand.  With her hand, I bid 2@h. 
The guideline I use is with a good 5 card suit, I need only about 10 points to come in freely over a third seat weak 2. 

And sometimes, if the suit is nice (or 6 cards), I will bid with even fewer HCP.  So 2@h looks OK.
If West bids 2@h, North should raise to 3@d - but in the actual auction, with 8+ losers, pass is probably OK.  
At matchpoints, however, I bid 3@d without any problem (Law of Total Tricks bid).|
