at|mitche:  East correctly balanced in with 2@S (you cannot afford to let your opponents steal from you)  and West's 
having not overcalled now comes back to haunt her. 
It turns out that 4@h is making, losing just a diamond and club ... and maybe a heart.

I guess the lessons are "it's a bidder's game" and "Don't be afraid to overcall a weak 2 with a good hand."  
If you wait for a better holding, you may wait a long time. You don’t need much more than T9x to win 4 trumps.


