at|mitche:  How should declarer think about the contract?
He has a sure trump loser and at least 3 diamond losers -- too many, and after the trump lead and continuation, he can 
ruff only once.
So let's "stand on our heads" and look at dummy as the "master hand" (Dummy Reversal)
Dummy has 3 clubs, 2 hearts, 1 diamond and a spade to worry about. (7 losers)
But what if declarer can win 5 hearts, the @CA, and ruff 2 clubs in his own hand?  That brings the count to 10 tricks.  
This means setting up the heart suit.  If @H's divide reasonably and Jack is in the West hand, it might work. |
